Hey y’all! I have been working on this email for the past week with no luck :sweat_smile: This is my first time trying dynamic content in a HS email.

I have a HubDB table uploaded and am trying to get info from the table to appear in my email for each recipient. TL:DR, we are sending emails alerting members of their new local reps, and have 40+ reps. I cannot spend my time building 40 unique emails, so this was the solve. Just trying to problem-solve getting their rep’s name to appear in the email. Would love any and all help and suggestions here!

```{% set query = "agm_name__eq="~agm_name %}
{% for agm in hubdb_table_rows(54884801, query) %}
{% set agm_name = contact_agm.name %}
&lt;span&gt;
&lt;p color="#FFFFFF" style="margin: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 22px;"&gt;
{{ agm_name }}         
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
{% endfor %}```
